Kaveel Singh, News24Durban - President Jacob Zuma has begun his address at the 6th Armed Forces Day celebrations in Durban. Zuma was welcomed at Moses Mabhida Stadium just after 10:00 on Tuesday by a traditional military parade. Speaking to News24 from the main podium area, military spokesperson Marumo Machete said a full day of military demonstrations was planned.He said that an assortment of military equipment would be on display for the public to observe. The SANDF has been at Durban's beachfront since last week, giving a number of military demonstrations to the public.President Jacob Zuma speaks at #ArmedForcesDay in Durban @News24 pic.twitter.com/vcoOHoxa0g&mdash; Kaveel Singh (@kaveels) February 21, 2017President Jacob Zuma speaks at #ArmedForcesDay in Durban @News24 pic.twitter.com/vcoOHoxa0g#ArmedForcesDay in memory of brave soldiers of SS Mendi we salute the SANDF @News24&mdash; Kaveel Singh (@kaveels) February 21, 2017#ArmedForcesDay in memory of brave soldiers of SS Mendi we salute the SANDF @News24Stoically disciplined military personnel listen to President Zuma as rain buckets down at Durban's #ArmedForcesDay @News24 pic.twitter.com/MexDpHHbxl&mdash; Kaveel Singh (@kaveels) February 21, 2017Stoically disciplined military personnel listen to President Zuma as rain buckets down at Durban's #ArmedForcesDay @News24 pic.twitter.com/MexDpHHbxlMilitary helicopters at #ArmedForcesDay @News24 pic.twitter.com/YQ04yzaCAG&mdash; Kaveel Singh (@kaveels) February 21, 2017Military helicopters at #ArmedForcesDay @News24 pic.twitter.com/YQ04yzaCAG24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.